0:[name]星来[line]Takky![%p]
100:[name]星来[line]Hey, Takky...[%p]
200:[name]星来[line]You can hear me, right?[%p]
300:[name]拓巳[line]Yeah, I can hear you, Seira-tan.[%p]
400:[name]星来[line]Listen, Takky, let's quit this game.[%p]
500:[name]拓巳[line]Game...[%p]
600:[name]星来[line]I know Nanami's your sister and you care about her, but it's probably too late.[%p]
700:[name]拓巳[line]T-That's not...[%p]
800:[name]拓巳[line]That's not true.[%p]
900:[name]星来[line]Think about it. If they cut off her arm, she'd die of blood loss, right? Maybe not in a video game, but in real life...[%p]
1000:[name]拓巳[line]Why... Why did Nanami have to...[%p]
1100:[name]星来[line]This is game over, I think.[%p]
1200:[name]星来[line]If you don't quit the game soon, more people will die.[%p]
1300:[name]拓巳[line]But... But you fight bad guys, too, don't you?[%p]
1400:[name]星来[line]That's because I'm...[%p]
1500:[name]星来[line]I'm an anime character! ♪[%p]
1600:I stuffed the Seira-tan figure into my uniform pocket.[%p]
1700:[name]拓巳[line]I have to save her. I have to...[%p]
1800:I'd brought Seira-tan to keep me safe.[%p]
1900:Normally, I'd never walk around with a figure in my pocket. It might get damaged, after all.[%p]
2000:Letting his wife be destroyed is the worst thing an otaku can do.[%p]
2100:But now, I didn't have it in me to follow my own policy. I needed something to keep me sane.[%p]
2200:Of course, I might be dead by this time tomorrow.[%p]
2300:I looked down at Seira-tan once more. Her head was poking out of my pocket. It helped me keep the tears from pouring out.[%p]
2400:Then somebody slammed into me from behind, and I staggered forward.[%p]
2500:I looked back and saw a DQN-type man looking at me, annoyed. But he disappeared into the crowd without saying another word.[%p]
2600:I looked around.[%p]
2700:I was in Shibuya's Scramble Crossing.[%p]
2800:It was hard to believe that it was 9:00 PM on a weekday, particularly only a few hours after an earthquake where over 100 people had died. There was an ocean of people around me.[%p]
2900:Just waiting for the light made me feel like I was going to suffocate. There were people everywhere, on all sides of me.[%p]
3000:I didn't know why, but the media was out here, too.[%p]
3100:There were people with big TV cameras stepping out onto the road, blocking traffic. The big lights they used for filming were everywhere, and they were blindingly bright.[%p]
3200:Several people who looked like newscasters were rapidly speaking into cameras.[%p]
3300:There were a few officers in uniform trying to keep the pedestrians and media out of the road, but the whole situation was out of control. The road was almost completely shut down from all the people on it.[%p]
3400:Was there an event or something going on? On a day like this, at this time of night?[%p]
3500:How could they hold something like that on a day where over 100 people had died? Did they not have the common decency to call it off? And why were the media here along with them?[%p]
3600:If its people were like this, Japan was doomed.[%p]
3700:Not that it mattered to me.[%p]
3800:[name]拓巳[line]I have to save her... I have to... save her.[%p]
3900:Shogun had sent me to O-FRONT, a building right in the middle of Scramble Crossing. It was the one with the TATSUYA and the Starbecks.[%p]
4000:I hadn't actually planned on going on my own. But I couldn't get a hold of Rimi at all.[%p]
4100:And the police might still think I was the NewGen killer, so I couldn't go to them, either.[%p]
4200:I was running out of time as I tried to figure out what to do. In the end, I got so worried about Nanami that I came here alone, with Seira-tan close at hand for protection.[%p]
4300:I worked my way through the crowds and inside O-FRONT.[%p]
4400:It was pretty crowded inside too, but I was too distracted to even care.[%p]
4500:All I could think about was Nanami's safety.[%p]
4600:I headed up the escalator to the floor above.[%p]
4700:There were big windows in the Starbecks that let you see out onto the square below. When I looked out of them, I could see just how many people there were in Scramble Crossing.[%p]
4800:It felt like everyone in the crowd was waving their arms or jumping up and down. An ocean of dark-haired heads roiled and bobbed beneath me.[%p]
4900:It was way brighter than it'd been when I was down there. I started to wonder if all the lights down below were facing toward the building I was in.[%p]
5000:Every time I took the escalator up another floor, my heart started pounding faster and faster.[%p]
5100:I took out my phone and checked the time. It was 9:01 PM.[%p]
5200:If Shogun got mad that I was late and killed Nanami... I shivered and ran up the escalator, pushing past the people in front of me.[%p]
5300:Halfway up, I switched to using the elevator, and took it to the top floor.[%p]
5400:I didn't know how I was going to get up to the roof from there, but I wandered around for a bit, trying to make sure nobody saw me, and eventually found an emergency staircase.[%p]
5500:I managed to get to the roof without anyone saying anything to me. It was a lot easier than I thought it would be.[%p]
5600:The wind was blowing hard on the roof. It felt strangely warm, considering it was the end of October. I realized quickly that it wasn't a natural wind, but the air blowing from the air conditioners on top of the building.[%p]
5700:I fastened the button on my pocket so Seira-tan wouldn't blow away.[%p]
5800:[name]星来[line]Thanks, dork![%p]
5900:[name]拓巳[line]Y-You're welcome.[%p]
6000:Hearing Seira-tan's voice in my brain made me feel a little better. A-As long as I had Seira-tan with me... I-I wasn't scared.[%p]
6100:That's what I told myself, over and over again.[%p]
6200:That said... It was awfully dark up here. The only light was the neon O-FRONT sign, which I was now seeing from behind.[%p]
6300:And the neon lights on the other buildings were so bright that it was hard to see around me. If somebody was hiding up here, I'd never be able to find them.[%p]
6400:[name]？？？[line]You're late.[%p]
6500:Someone suddenly spoke. My heartbeat had been starting to slow, but now it flew back up to top speed.[%p]
6600:I looked around, but it was too dark to see where the speaker was.[%p]
6700:I heard a sound. It was the creaking sound I'd heard so many times before.[%p]
6800:This time, I slowly trained my eyes on the darkness in front of me. I could barely make out the outline of a wheelchair's wheels against the light.[%p]
6900:[name]拓巳[line]Ah...[%p]
7000:Shogun...[%p]
7100:[name]将軍[line]Welcome, Takumi.[%p]
7200:The voice was friendly as it said my name. It made me feel sick.[%p]
7300:I didn't want to talk to Shogun. I was scared. I wanted to run away from here right now.[%p]
7400:[name]星来[line]Let's run away, then![%p]
7500:[name]星来[line]He's going to kill you if you don't run, Takky![%p]
7600:But Nanami...[%p]
